I created my digital literacy infographic using Canva, which is a user-friendly online design tool. 
The infographic is designed as a one-page visual resource to help students understand the importance of digital literacy in today’s world. 
It covers key topics such as the meaning of digital literacy, useful digital tools for students, safe internet practices, professional online presence, and email etiquette. 
Each section is presented with short, clear points along with relevant icons to make the information visually appealing and easy to understand.
While designing the infographic, I focused on keeping the layout simple and organized so that viewers can quickly grasp the main ideas. 
One interesting aspect of using Canva was exploring different templates and design elements that enhanced the overall presentation. 
However, I found it slightly challenging to fit all important information into a single page without making it look cluttered.
This task helped me understand how to present information effectively in a concise and visually engaging way.
